result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Todd L Mueller

records.descr: Records of prosec. are converted data. See file.

records.addlTxt: from DA Blader w/Attachments Re: Amendment to Order for PSI to Include DRI of Companion Case No. 2015CF000171

12:07 pm cases called. 15CF47, 15CF109, 15CF171, & 15TR685. Defendant Todd L Mueller in court with attorney Matthew Loren Goldin.  Defendant Todd L Mueller in custody.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Global resolution reached on all pending matters. Agreement read into record by DA Blader. Attorney Goldin concurs.  15CF109-Preliminary hearing discussed-defendant wishes to waive right to preliminary hearing. Court questions defendant regarding waiver of right to preliminary hearing. Court accepts waiver, finds probable cause and enters an order binding defendant over for trial. Information filed. Attorney Goldin confirms receipt, waives formal reading.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: No Contest to Count 1 of 15CF54 & No Contest to 15CF109.   Court dismisses outright Count 2 of 15CF54. Court dismisses and reads-in 15CF171 & 15TR685. Court revokes bond and requests sentencing hearing be scheduled.  Court accepts plea and orders a PSI be completed.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for February 16, 2016 at 09:00 am.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.  No operation of any motor vehicles whatsoever.
Defendant and Atty Szilagyi appear via video.

Case called @ 1:03 p.m. Defendant Todd L Mueller in court, in custody, appears via video with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant will be represented by SPD. DA Blader requesting $10,000 Cash Bond. Atty Szilagyi requesting $5000-$7500 Cash Bond. Court orders $10,000 Cash Bond. IA Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State. The Court notes that he was a witness to this case and will recuse himself if and when the need arises. Attorney Szilagyi expresses a concern that there may now be a conflict with Atty Goldin proceeding as the attorney of record based on the newly filed matter.  Initial appearance scheduled for December 3, 2015 at 12:00 pm.
